+ After wally world Dan and I went to see walking tall. It was funny. Plus the Rock is so sexy ya know.  Then we went to mcdonalds cause it was the only place that was open on Easter. That makes 5 out of the 7 days this week i have had fast food for dinner. I'm on pace to die next year.

-I blew all of my paycheck this weekend already. That's very depressing. Whatevvvv.

-We have school tomorrow

+ I don't think im going.

+ I have finally gotten a band going.

-Weird Al's parents died.



Well thats my update. I love you guys.

X Fest= Story of the Year AND Switchfoot AND Offspring. Im so there. It's only 25 bucs. Id pay 25 bucs alone to see story of the year. Other bands are Drowning Pool-yuck. Cypress Hill-Yuck. New Found Glory-Yay. Punchline-Yay. Finger eleven-Yay.


And there are still many bands to be announced. But it's already great.

I'm pretty sleepy. I woke up at 9:00 this morning because some guy came to fix some leak in the basement. He felt the need to pound on the door 50 million times harder then necessary. Now i'm just waiting to go to work. 5-11:30. Woopee. Last night Ashley came over and we went to giant eagle and bought popcicles! Popcicles rule hardcore. And fruity pebbles, and cheeeese ballllsss, and gatorade. Everything we were in the mood for. And we had a little party by ourselves. It was nice. Very nice. 

     I was looking foward to cici's pizza with brian ben and michelle. But since i'm so nice, i told some girl id work for her. But since she's so nice she wont work for me tomorrow. Being nice to people gets you nowhere. Seriously. It just makes people take advantage of you...

Hey, this weekend was cool.

     Friday Dan H, Dan L, Greg and myself went to cici's all you can eat pizza buffet. Then we went to k-mart and tried to buy a bb gun to shoot cows with, but no such luck. So we went to gregs house and watched the pitt game while conversing about different things. I found myself growing bored, so i went to Brians house. We played x-box for awhile, finished watching the pitt game.

   Saturday I asked brian if he would go see grease with me, since I had a major obligation to go. He reluctantly agreed. It was ok. Musicals never hold my attention, so Brian and I played an hour long game of rock paper scissors, followed by thumb wrestling, followed by cell phone games. No offense to anyone who was in the musical. Those sort of things dont hold my interest. Accept the wizard of oz last year was very good. I think the major problem with this years musical was they did a horrible job picking the cast. Nobody played their role very well. Ashley did very very very very good though. I was very proud of her. And so did lynds! Im very sorry i didn't dance on the stage with you lynds. I was just very comfy in my seat. I regret not doing it now. Jackie did very good too. But when you guys were not on the stage, I was zZzZzZzZ.

     Last night at work ruled. It was sooo slow. Steph and I called papa johns and told them if they brought us pizza we would give them ice cream. So basically we just pigged out on pizza and ice cream. It was like a birthday party.


   This week sucks ass. More PSSA's. BLAAHH. 

Later buds

Today was an extremely uneventful day, considering how today was a rather significant event. So being how great i am, I sat around and planned a great special day for us. But due to our schools dumb choir teacher, nothing special is happening.  Because as I remembered to call off work, I guess she can't get off of choir, so March 4th 2004, our two year anniversary will be spent writing a god damn scarlet letter essay, and watching survivor. But I tried.

    The Darkness is sold out. That sucks hardcore.

    
     I have to work tomorrow. How awesome is that. I have to work Saturday how aweomse is that. I have to work Sunday how awesome is that.

It was was a nice warm day today. Things were lookin pretty chipper. But i'll be the first to tell you that a shitty lunch can have a big effect on your day...

    We've started schedulin at the ol' ringgold high school. That time of year again. Hurrs what im takin

College English 12
Public Speaking 11-12
Trig/Pre Calculus
AP Biology
AP American History
Multimedia Productions
Video Production 1
Gym/Study Hall
Fine Art 1 or Current Issues <--- not sure about this one yet

Next Year is not looking easy! I dont plan on missing much school next year, since it's my last year of high school.

Tonight I am meeting dear Nicole at the mall for a bit of shopping! I just need to get out of the house. I don't have work tonight, and im really bored. I really should study for my Scarlet Letter test in english. Or do my Scarlet Letter essay. Or do my research paper. Or not. 

Later kids

I basically have been caught up in the same old tangent all week. We had to take PSSA tests. This year they are put on our college transcripts. Congrats Pennsylvania, your officially the stupidest most worthless state ever...
So anyway, it's been pssa's and work. Work has been very intersting to say the least. One of my managers likes to sneak her friends into the walk-in freezer and get high. Seriously, if you can't even wait until you get home to get high, then you're a really big loser. 

    Although my week has struggled, my weekend has ruled. I spent the night with my sweetheart. We went and saw "The passon of the Christ". It was a good movie, but i didn't like it. It was very sad, and the whole point of it was to make you feel extremely guilty. It was very well directed. But no. It wasnt a movie i would ever watch again. I just really wanted to see what all the hype was about. I believe in God and everything, i just don't like religious movies.

    Today I worked. Tonight I had one of the funniest nights I have had in a long time. I hung out with Brian, Frank and Ryan. And we went out to dinner. Then we commited a Federal Offense and I hope we don't get put in jail. Though it was the funniest crime ever commited. I'd rather not mention it though. After that we went back to Brians house and played RISK!!!!! Hahahaa, very fun night.

     I'm worn out. It is bed time. I love you everybody <3.

Work sucked last night. It was super busy. I can't stand the public as a whole. People are so bitchy. I know im contridicting myself when I say this, because I am guilty in many aspects of this public stereotype as well. The difference between Bruster's and fast food restaurants, is that everything gets sent back. You do one thing wrong, it gets sent back. If one milk shake is too milky, it gets sent back. Not enough hot fudge? Damn that bitch is coming back. I find it horribly irritating. Usually at fast food restaurants, a lot of times people will just grunt and deal with it. I think part of the reason is that I work in Bethel Park, and many people in Bethel Park are snobs. It just amazes me how someone can so grumpy over their ice cream cone being messy! I mean its ice cream! How isn't ice cream messy? Everyone is so picky. It's  annoying, but it's not going to stop me from lovin that job. That job rules.

I am super bummed. Today was horrible. School was ok. When I got home I slept and slept. I woke up 10 minutes before i had to leave for work. My last pair of contacts ripped, i had to work tonight with one eye closed. And my dog is dying tomorrow. OH YEAH. My parents decided to make an appointment to kill my dog tomorrow morning. Isn't that lovely? and I just hear about it last night. Granted, he can no longer hold his bladder, he has trouble walking, and he pukes once a day. But this is one of that saddest things I have ever gone through. My parents are heartless. Just heartless. I grew up with my dog. He's as old as my sister. He's been around since i was 4. I'm just crushed. JUST FUCKING CRUSHED>!LK()#H!*UI(NKM LD:m;nq9$&^Y*(

To put it mildly, today was a not so good day. Everything would be perfect right now, if I could just somehow muster up a way to stop the constant conflict with my parents. But I'm really coming to the conclusion, that no matter how much I get blamed for, and no matter how much they say I do wrong, nothing they say is true. I mean, after we fight, I will try so hard to think of what I did wrong, but there is nothing. I understand a lot of people feel this way about their parents, but damn, I would bet my life that I'm right. It's pretty horrible. 

    After my day started off with a fight with my mother, Brian and I went to pizza hut for the pizza hut buffet, which was yummy.

    Then I had my first day at work. It's pretty cool. It's a lot of fun, just a bit challenging. They make over 500 different types of ice cream, but they only serve 24 at a time. Which is really cool, but honestly i'm not a huge ice cream fan. I love sherbert. And i like a few flavors, but i'm not a big fan of it. The job seems pretty easy though, the people there are pretty nice.

    I'm so worn out, both physically and mentally, and it's taking its toll. I hate having to be dependent on my parents. I hate the thought. They shove every little thing they do for me down my throat. But you know, it was they who accidently brought me into this cruel nasty world, so as far as i'm concerned, they fucking owe me a lot. That might not be a good attitude, but it's the truth.

                Goodnight

Today was senior skip day.
I didnt skip, cause i'm not a senior. But the rest of the school did...

Which made today a pretty easy day. I spent the entire afternoon doing stuff for mrs. garry. The morning wasn't bad either. Very long and drawn out...


I start work tomorrow. I'd normally be nervous, but the people that work there are idiots, so its ok if i act like an idiot, cause i'd fit right in. Before I go, Brian and i are heading to the all you can eat pizza buffet at pizza hut, which is a HORRIBLE idea, due to the fact that I have to go to work straight from there. My stomachs gonna be killing me. Hehe....

                     Later kids,
                           Austin

Today ruled. It started off as a long dreary day, but as soon as I got home from school, I headed to k-mart to look for something for my baby for v-day. Dan called, and he came to k-mart. Then our dinner consisted of the dollar menu at wendys. We are the fast food kings. It's not unlike us to hit up 2 or 3 fast food restaurants in one day. Very unhealthy though. After that Mike came over for an hour or two to get a brief beating in madden. Then I was exhausted so i took a nap. During my nap Jesse called and I went to his house for a few hours. Came home, did my daily quarrel with my parents. Blah blah blah BLAH.

I hate graduation project period days. I'm going to school late tomorrow. :/

I felt much better today. Well I did until a half hour after I woke up. Before I tell you this story, i have to start with another one:

     I no longer have a good relationship with my dad. I mean, I would love too, and I try all the time too, but its useless. We had a good relationship up until 2 years ago, and then for some reason it just went down hill. The only time my dad speaks to me is when he says "GEEETTT AAA JOOOBBB". Now that you know this information I will begin my story

     So today I woke up. Called my baby, and my call waiting beeped. What do you know, ITS BRUSTERS!!!!!!!!!!!!!! They called and asked me to come in  for an interview. I went downstairs and told my dad I needed his car to go for an interview. I was so excited, cause I thought my dad would like me if i had a job. Boy was I mistaken. He flipped out on me, because Brusters is 15 minutes away. Which makes no sense, because the other places I applied at are like 20 minutes away, and he oked those. Anyway, I flipped out on me, screamed, yelled and what not, because it was 15 minutes away. Jesus. He doesnt want me wasting his gas. There is seriously no pleasing him. I really can't take it. So I go for the interview and I get the job. YAAAY. I start Friday. I got my bruster's shirt, and I got my bruster's hat. it's gonna be cool. I'm the only guy that works there, it's all girlies. It seems pretty cool. I only work 3 days a week. Anyway, I come home, and I ask my mom if i can go to the library. Here was our convo

Me: Mom can I go to the library?
Mom: No. You will probably go somewhere else. You dont even like to read.
Me: Yes I Do! Where else would i go?
Mom: I dunno. You might go do drugs. You just know i'll say yes if you go to the library. I bet your going to go do drugs, so no.
Me: I HAVE NEVER DONE DRUGS!?

So cool man. Now im accused of doing things I have never even done. We got in a huge fight, and now i'm not allowed to drive her car, but I have to pay 70 dollars a month for my car insurance. Hmmm something doesnt seem right. I pay 70 dollars a month, and i'm not even allowed to drive the god damn car. WOOOO. I love life. My mom is pyscho. She seriously needs help. My dads a jerk. I don't know how I am supposed to operate with parents who are half retarded...

     Well anyway, after that, Mike came over and we filmed cribs. After we filmed cribs, we played ps2 and ate 3 boxes of gushers.

Tonight my baby is coming over tonight to calm me down from the psychoness my parents thrust upon me.

I'm pretty sick, and i'm pretty worn out, and I have nothing to do. I'm not a happy camper. :/. Today just consisted of laying around, and doing nothing. I got 12 hours of sleep last night which ruled, and I probably added another 3-4 on to that total today. Ashley and I were supposed to have a slumber party tonight, but her Great Grandmother passed away and I haven't heard from her since after school yesterday. I don't know how she is, or where she is. All I know is that she is not home and I miss her :(. Tonight I watched Gone in 60 seconds, followed by edward scissor hands, followed by the lion king. BLaaaaaH. I love the lion king though. That movie's a classic.

     Last night Brian and I went to see Miracle, but it was sold out. So we got some unique food at the mall, and of course i stocked up on gummy bears!!!!! Then I went back to his house and we played x-box, and made fun of michelle. Heh.

Tomorrow Mike's coming over and were filming cribs at my house for video production. AHAHHAAHAHHAHHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAH

I'm going to update again tonight with another depressing lonley entry.

Falling in love
It was the best idea I ever had

I skipped school today, due to the extreme amount of homework I did not complete. This weekend definatly ruled. Friday-ice skating. On Saturday Brian and I went to the movies. We saw the butterfly effect. <--- awesome movie!!! I hate Ashton Kutcher, man, but it ruled. Sunday, Ashee came over. We played in the snow, then took a nap. :). Naps are the best. Then she left. I watched some of the Super Bowl, but it wasn't exciting, so I picked up kayla and we went joy riding. We got ice cream in 11 degree weather, and I put in an application at Brusters.

Today i am lonley.

Whew am I sore. I went ice skating tonight with Ash. It's been quite sometime since ive ice skated. I didnt fall, however, my movement was not smooth and steady, it was very spuratic and unpredicatable. It was fun though. Before that I stopped over to see my grandma. It's been awhile since Ive talked to her, so I bought her some carrot cake and stopped by to see her. It was nice. 

I'm waay to tired to write anything. Or even think. I get very crabby and bitter when im tired also, so the best bet would be to go to bed.

Bo-Ring night. Nothing to do :(. I took my sister to mcdonalds and we got sum fooood. Thats the highlight.

I finally got the switchfoot album entitled "The Beautiful Let down". Some GOOOD STUFF.

"It's not looking too good for you" Remarked my father, as he peered out the window looking for the itty bitty little snow flurries.
"It's hardly snowing!" I replied
"YES IT IS! I WAS JUST OUT THERE." Shot back my father
I sighed.
"DONT BLAME ME FOR THE WEATHER" He harshly added.


See...I've had this problem with my parents, and this phase they are going through. I like to call it the "fibbing/exaggerating phase". This phase only pops up when I want to use the car. My dad loves to use weather as an excuse why I can't use the car. He will call me from work and say "Dont think your going anywhere, where supposed to get a huge snow storm tonight." Meanwhile I watch the weather and all they are calling for is flueries. I have literally asked my dad to go somewhere before, and he has told me no, and I have asked why, and he has said "Because its too cold". I just don't know how I am supposed to deal with such ridiculous childish behavior. I sent a very detailed e-mail to Dr. Phil asking him if he would have my parents and I on his show to help fix this problem of theirs.

I haven't updated in awhile.

New Years was quite a trip. Ashley and I went to Brian's party, which was fun, but nothing out of the ordinary. I was really hoping for alcohol, but there was a very limited amount. We just played air hockey and beat the shit out of each other like we always do. We left around 12:30, and went back to my house. Ashley stayed over...We didn't really sleep. We stayed up all night talking. We layed in my room together and just talked. We would go from laughing and being happy, to crying and being sad. It was a very starry-eyed night, as we just laid their with the only light being that of my neon guitar light. I found out things about her that I never knew before, and i've dated her for a year and 10 or 11 months. I loved last night. I really loved it. But after we have a great night like last night, I find myself missing her like hell. I want to talk to her and be with her every second of the day. We are 16, and I shouldn't feel like that at 16 years old. I shouldnt constantly feel the need to be with her, and that's what makes it so scary and confusing. So I try to seperate myself from her, by exposing my mind to all the bad thoughts, and bad situations that have happened between us. Which also leaves me miserable. It's nights like these that leave me utterly confused. The majority of my journal entrys are of this kind, but it's the major thing going on in my life right now.

But I have a really hard time getting too close with her again. It's kind of like...one big mind game. Which isn't really nice.  Last night I went to the Pens game with my dad. Its nice to do something with my dad once in awhile.


I really despise this time of the year. Right after Christmas sucks. I really don't like January-March. It's just cold and miserable. New YEars is my least favorite holiday. I don't like it at all.
